<Layout
    title="Privacy Policy — Consultologist"
    description="How Mortigen Inc. (Consultologist.AI) collects, uses, and protects personal information on consultologist.ai and app.consultologist.ai."
>
    <article class="article-page">
        <header class="article-header">
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="article-meta">Last updated July 9, 2026</p>
        </header>
        <div class="article-prose">
            <p>
                This Privacy Notice for <strong>Mortigen Inc.</strong> (doing business as
                <strong>Consultologist.AI</strong>) ("<strong>we</strong>", "<strong>us</strong>",
                or "<strong>our</strong>") describes how and why we might access, collect, store,
                use, and/or share ("<strong>process</strong>") your personal information when you
                use our services ("<strong>Services</strong>"), including when you:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Visit our website at <a href="https://consultologist.ai">consultologist.ai</a>,
                    or any website of ours that links to this Privacy Notice
                </li>
                <li>
                    Use <strong>Consultologist</strong>, our application at
                    <a href="https://app.consultologist.ai">app.consultologist.ai</a> — a platform
                    that helps specialist physicians create consultation notes
                </li>
                <li>Engage with us in other related ways, including marketing or events</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                <strong>Questions or concerns?</strong> Reading this Privacy Notice will help you
                understand your privacy rights and choices. We are responsible for making
                decisions about how your personal information is processed. If you do not agree
                with our policies and practices, please do not use our Services. If you still
                have questions or concerns, contact us at
                <a href="/contact">tauheed[dot]elahee[at]consultologist[dot]ai</a>.
            </p>

            <h2>Summary of key points</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>What personal information do we process?</strong> Contact and account
                    information you provide, and limited technical information collected
                    automatically. See <a href="#infocollect">Section 1</a>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Do we process sensitive information?</strong> The application
                    processes clinical referral content submitted by physician users, which may
                    contain patient health information. We treat this with specific safeguards —
                    see <a href="#referral-content">Section 4</a>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Do we collect information from third parties?</strong> No. We do not
                    purchase or collect information about you from data brokers, public
                    databases, or social media platforms.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>How do we process your information?</strong> To provide and improve
                    the Services, communicate with you, keep the Services secure, and comply
                    with law. See <a href="#infouse">Section 2</a>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>When and with whom do we share information?</strong> With the service
                    providers that run our infrastructure — principally Microsoft Azure. We do
                    not sell personal information or share it with advertisers. See
                    <a href="#whoshare">Section 5</a>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>What are your rights?</strong> Depending on where you live, you may
                    have rights to access, correct, or delete your personal information. See
                    <a href="#privacyrights">Section 12</a>.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>How do you exercise your rights?</strong> The easiest way is via
                    <a href="/contact">consultologist.ai/contact</a> or by emailing us.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Table of contents</h2>
            <ol>
                <li><a href="#infocollect">What information do we collect?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#infouse">How do we process your information?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#legalbases">What legal bases do we rely on to process your information?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#referral-content">Patient information in referral content</a></li>
                <li><a href="#whoshare">When and with whom do we share your personal information?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#cookies">Do we use cookies and other tracking technologies?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#ai">Do we offer artificial intelligence-based products?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#sociallogins">How do we handle your logins?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#inforetain">How long do we keep your information?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#infosafe">How do we keep your information safe?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#infominors">Do we collect information from minors?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#privacyrights">What are your privacy rights?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#dnt">Controls for Do-Not-Track features</a></li>
                <li><a href="#policyupdates">Do we make updates to this notice?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#contact">How can you contact us about this notice?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#request">How can you review, update, or delete your data?</a></li>
            </ol>

            <h2 id="infocollect">1. What information do we collect?</h2>
            <h3>Personal information you disclose to us</h3>
            <p><em><strong>In short:</strong> we collect personal information that you provide to us.</em></p>
            <p>
                We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide when you register
                for the application, join the waitlist or contact us through our website, or
                otherwise communicate with us. Depending on how you interact with the Services,
                this may include:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>names</li>
                <li>email addresses</li>
                <li>job titles and medical specialty</li>
                <li>institution or clinic name</li>
                <li>authentication data from your sign-in provider</li>
                <li>contact preferences</li>
                <li>anything you choose to write in the contact form's comments field</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                <strong>Payments.</strong> We do not currently sell paid subscriptions or process
                payments, and we do not collect payment card information. If this changes, we
                will update this notice first.
            </p>
            <p>
                All personal information that you provide to us must be true, complete, and
                accurate, and you must notify us of any changes to it.
            </p>
            <h3>Information automatically collected</h3>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> some technical information — such as your IP
                address and browser characteristics — is collected automatically when you use
                the Services.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                We automatically collect certain information when you visit, use, or navigate
                the Services. This information does not reveal your specific identity but may
                include device and usage information such as IP address, browser and device
                characteristics, operating system, referring URLs, and information about how and
                when you use the Services. It is primarily needed to keep the Services secure
                and operating, and for internal analytics. This includes:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <em>Log and usage data.</em> Service-related, diagnostic, usage, and
                    performance information our servers collect automatically, such as request
                    logs, error reports, and feature usage.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <em>Device data.</em> Information about the computer or device you use to
                    access the Services, such as IP address, browser type, operating system, and
                    system configuration.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We do not collect precise geolocation, and we do not obtain information about
                you from data brokers, public databases, marketing partners, or social media
                platforms.
            </p>

            <h2 id="infouse">2. How do we process your information?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> we process your information to provide, improve,
                and administer the Services, communicate with you, keep the Services secure, and
                comply with law.</em>
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>To facilitate account creation and authentication</strong> and
                    otherwise manage user accounts, including enabling accounts as we admit beta
                    testers.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>To deliver the Services</strong> — most importantly, to generate
                    consultation note drafts from the referral content you submit.
                </li>
                <li><strong>To respond to inquiries and offer support.</strong></li>
                <li>
                    <strong>To send administrative information</strong> such as changes to our
                    terms and policies.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>To contact you about availability and updates</strong> if you joined
                    the waitlist or asked to be contacted — you can opt out at any time.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>To request feedback</strong> about your use of the Services,
                    particularly during the beta.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>To post reviews or testimonials</strong> on our website, only with
                    the reviewer's consent.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>To protect the Services</strong>, including spam prevention, fraud
                    monitoring, and abuse prevention.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>To evaluate and improve the Services</strong>, including identifying
                    usage trends and fixing defects.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="legalbases">3. What legal bases do we rely on to process your information?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> we only process your personal information when we
                have a valid legal reason to do so — such as your consent, compliance with laws,
                providing you with services, protecting your rights, or our legitimate business
                interests.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                We may process your information if you have given us specific permission
                (express consent) to use it for a specific purpose, or in situations where your
                permission can be inferred (implied consent). You can
                <a href="#privacyrights">withdraw your consent</a> at any time.
            </p>
            <p>
                In some exceptional cases, we may be legally permitted under applicable law to
                process your information without your consent — for example: if collection is
                clearly in the interests of an individual and consent cannot be obtained in a
                timely way; for investigations and fraud detection and prevention; for business
                transactions provided certain conditions are met; if disclosure is required to
                comply with a subpoena, warrant, court order, or rules of the court; if the
                information was produced by an individual in the course of their employment,
                business, or profession and the collection is consistent with the purposes for
                which it was produced; or if the information is publicly available and specified
                by regulations.
            </p>

            <h2 id="referral-content">4. Patient information in referral content</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> the application processes clinical text submitted
                by physician users, which may contain patient health information. We process it
                solely to provide the service, and we do not use it to train AI models.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                Consultologist's core function is turning a referral package — text a physician
                pastes into the application — into a draft consultation note. That text may
                contain personal health information about patients. In respect of that
                information:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Physician users remain the health information custodians of their patients'
                    information under applicable health privacy law (such as Ontario's PHIPA).
                    We process referral content as a service provider on the physician's behalf,
                    solely to provide the Services.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Referral content and generated notes are processed and stored on Microsoft
                    Azure infrastructure. Consult generation uses Microsoft Azure AI services
                    (see <a href="#ai">Section 7</a>); the content is not used to train AI
                    models.
                </li>
                <li>
                    We do not sell, share for marketing, or otherwise use referral content for
                    any purpose beyond providing and securing the Services.
                </li>
                <li>
                    The application keeps a history of consult generation jobs for the
                    physician's own record and review; physicians can request deletion of their
                    account and its data (see <a href="#request">Section 16</a>).
                </li>
                <li>
                    During early access, deployments are set up with each clinic so that data
                    handling meets the clinic's privacy and security requirements. Ask us about
                    the specifics for your site.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="whoshare">5. When and with whom do we share your personal information?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> we share information only with the service
                providers that run our infrastructure, and in limited legal situations. We do
                not sell personal information, and we do not share it with advertising
                networks.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                We may share your data with third-party vendors, service providers, or agents
                ("<strong>third parties</strong>") who perform services for us or on our behalf
                and require access to such information to do that work. The third parties we use
                are:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Cloud hosting and infrastructure:</strong> Microsoft Azure (website
                    and application hosting, storage, backups, and monitoring via Azure
                    Application Insights)
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>AI services:</strong> Microsoft Azure AI (consult draft generation —
                    see <a href="#ai">Section 7</a>)
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Authentication:</strong> Microsoft Entra ID (Microsoft accounts) and
                    LinkedIn OAuth, when you use them to sign in to the application
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Email delivery:</strong> Azure Communication Services (contact-form
                    and service emails)
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Security and spam prevention:</strong> Cloudflare Turnstile, which
                    verifies that contact-form submissions come from humans
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Web analytics:</strong> Microsoft Clarity, which we may use to
                    understand how visitors use our website (see
                    <a href="#cookies">Section 6</a>)
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>We may also need to share personal information in the following situations:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Business transfers.</strong> We may share or transfer your
                    information in connection with, or during negotiations of, any merger, sale
                    of company assets, financing, or acquisition of all or a portion of our
                    business to another company.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="cookies">6. Do we use cookies and other tracking technologies?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> we use a small number of strictly functional
                technologies today, and no advertising cookies at all.</em>
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Preferences:</strong> the website stores your light/dark theme choice
                    in your browser's local storage. It never leaves your device.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Security:</strong> Cloudflare Turnstile runs on our contact form to
                    block automated spam, and may set technical cookies for that purpose.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Sessions:</strong> the application stores authentication tokens in
                    your browser so you stay signed in.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Analytics:</strong> we may use Microsoft Clarity on the website to
                    understand how pages are used (for example, which sections visitors read).
                    Clarity sets analytics cookies and may record anonymized interaction data;
                    form fields are masked. We will keep this section current with the tools we
                    actually run.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We do not use advertising, retargeting, or cross-site tracking technologies.
                Most web browsers accept cookies by default; you can usually set your browser to
                remove or reject them, though some features of the Services may not work without
                the functional ones.
            </p>

            <h2 id="ai">7. Do we offer artificial intelligence-based products?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> yes — AI-assisted consult drafting is the
                product. It runs on Microsoft Azure AI services.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                Consultologist provides features powered by artificial intelligence
                ("<strong>AI Products</strong>"): generating draft consultation note sections
                from referral content, text analysis, and related natural-language processing.
                We provide these through Microsoft Azure AI services ("<strong>AI Service
                Provider</strong>"). Your input and output are processed by the AI Service
                Provider within our Azure environment to provide the Services, under agreements
                that do not permit its use to train their models. The AI models we run may
                include open-weight models from third-party developers (such as DeepSeek),
                hosted entirely within our Microsoft Azure environment — no data is sent to, or
                shared with, the developers of those models.
            </p>
            <p>
                Every AI-generated draft is presented to the physician for review, editing, and
                sign-off; nothing enters a clinical record without the physician's approval. You
                must not use the AI Products in any way that violates the terms or policies of
                the AI Service Provider.
            </p>

            <h2 id="sociallogins">8. How do we handle your logins?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> if you sign in with a Microsoft or LinkedIn
                account, we receive certain profile information from that provider.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                The application offers registration and sign-in using third-party identity
                providers (such as a Microsoft account via Microsoft Entra ID, or LinkedIn).
                Where you choose this, we receive certain profile information from the provider
                — typically your name and email address. We use this information only for the
                purposes described in this notice. We do not control, and are not responsible
                for, the provider's own use of your information; review their privacy notices to
                understand their practices.
            </p>

            <h2 id="inforetain">9. How long do we keep your information?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> for as long as necessary to provide the Services,
                unless a longer period is required by law.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                We keep your personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes set
                out in this notice, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by
                law. No purpose in this notice requires keeping your personal information longer
                than the period in which you have an account with us. When we have no ongoing
                legitimate business need to process your personal information, we will delete or
                anonymize it — or, if that is not possible (for example, because it is held in
                backup archives), we will securely store it, isolated from further processing,
                until deletion is possible.
            </p>

            <h2 id="infosafe">10. How do we keep your information safe?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> through organisational and technical security
                measures — though no system can be guaranteed 100% secure.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                We have implemented appropriate and reasonable technical and organisational
                security measures designed to protect the personal information we process.
                However, no electronic transmission over the Internet or information storage
                technology can be guaranteed to be completely secure, so we cannot promise that
                unauthorised third parties will never defeat our security. Transmission of
                personal information to and from our Services is at your own risk; access the
                Services only within a secure environment.
            </p>

            <h2 id="infominors">11. Do we collect information from minors?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> we do not knowingly collect data from or market
                to anyone under 18 years of age.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                We do not knowingly collect, solicit data from, or market to children under 18
                years of age (or the equivalent age specified by law in your jurisdiction). By
                using the Services, you represent that you are at least 18. If we learn that
                personal information from users under 18 has been collected, we will deactivate
                the account and take reasonable measures to delete the data promptly. If you
                become aware of any data we may have collected from children, contact us at
                <a href="/contact">tauheed[dot]elahee[at]consultologist[dot]ai</a>.
                (This age restriction applies to users of the Services; it does not restrict the
                ages of patients whose information appears in referral content submitted by
                physicians.)
            </p>

            <h2 id="privacyrights">12. What are your privacy rights?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> in some regions, such as Canada, you have rights
                that allow you greater access to and control over your personal
                information.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                Depending on applicable law, you may have the right to request access to and
                obtain a copy of your personal information, request correction or erasure,
                restrict its processing, and, if applicable, request data portability. In
                certain circumstances you may also have the right to object to the processing of
                your personal information. You can make such a request by contacting us using
                the details in <a href="#contact">Section 15</a>. We will consider and act upon
                any request in accordance with applicable data protection laws.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Withdrawing your consent:</strong> if we rely on your consent — express
                or implied — you can withdraw it at any time by contacting us. This will not
                affect the lawfulness of processing before the withdrawal.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Opting out of marketing:</strong> you can unsubscribe from marketing
                communications at any time by using the unsubscribe link in our emails or by
                contacting us. We may still send you service-related messages necessary for the
                administration of your account.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Account information:</strong> you can review or change your account
                information by logging in to your account settings, or request termination of
                your account by contacting us. On termination we will deactivate or delete your
                account and information from our active databases, though we may retain some
                information to prevent fraud, troubleshoot problems, assist with investigations,
                enforce our legal terms, and/or comply with legal requirements.
            </p>

            <h2 id="dnt">13. Controls for Do-Not-Track features</h2>
            <p>
                Most web browsers include a Do-Not-Track ("DNT") setting to signal your
                preference not to have your online browsing monitored. No uniform technology
                standard for recognising DNT signals has been finalised, and we do not currently
                respond to them. If a standard is adopted that we must follow, we will inform
                you in a revised version of this notice.
            </p>

            <h2 id="policyupdates">14. Do we make updates to this notice?</h2>
            <p>
                <em><strong>In short:</strong> yes, as necessary to stay compliant with relevant
                laws.</em>
            </p>
            <p>
                We may update this Privacy Notice from time to time. The updated version will be
                indicated by the "Last updated" date at the top. If we make material changes, we
                may notify you by prominently posting a notice or by contacting you directly. We
                encourage you to review this notice frequently.
            </p>

            <h2 id="contact">15. How can you contact us about this notice?</h2>
            <p>
                If you have questions or comments about this notice, you may contact our Data
                Protection Officer by email at
                <a href="/contact">tauheed[dot]elahee[at]consultologist[dot]ai</a>.
            </p>

            <h2 id="request">16. How can you review, update, or delete your data?</h2>
            <p>
                You have the right to request access to the personal information we collect from
                you, details about how we have processed it, correction of inaccuracies, or
                deletion of your personal information. You may also have the right to withdraw
                your consent to our processing. These rights may be limited in some
                circumstances by applicable law. To make a request, visit
                <a href="/contact">consultologist.ai/contact</a> or email us.
            </p>

            <p>
                <em>
                    This Privacy Policy was created using
                    <a href="https://termly.io/products/privacy-policy-generator/" rel="noopener"
                        >Termly's Privacy Policy Generator</a
                    > and adapted to describe our Services.
                </em>
            </p>
        </div>
